## Medium Severity Findings

### 5. Eager Test — `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` (line 54)

```csharp
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
```

**Risk:** 7 distinct production methods called. A failure in any one produces a vague diagnostic — you don't know which step broke. This test is doing the job of 7 tests.

**Fix:** Either split into focused unit tests for each method, or — if this is intentionally an integration/workflow test — rename it clearly and keep it alongside focused unit tests:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ValidateOrder_WithItems_Succeeds()
{
    var processor = new OrderProcessor(_db, _email, _inventory);
    var order = new Order { Items = { new OrderItem("SKU-1", 2) } };

    processor.ValidateOrder(order);

    Assert.AreEqual("Validated", order.Status);
}
// ... separate tests for CalculateTotal, ApplyDiscount, etc.
```

