## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Test | Effort | Why first |
|----------|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free | `CompletesWithoutError` | Low | False-pass risk — this test catches nothing today |
| 2 | Conditional Logic | `SetsCorrectStatus` | Low | Hidden untested branch — split into two tests |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | `AsyncNotification_IsSent` | Low | Slows CI by 2s and is flaky by nature |
| 4 | Mystery Guest | `ImportOrders_FromCsv` | Low | Broken on every machine except the author's |
| 5 | Exception Handling | `EmptyOrder_ThrowsValidationError` | Low | Quick mechanical refactor to `ThrowsException<T>` |
| 6 | Sensitive Equality | `ReturnsFormattedString` | Low | Swap `.ToString()` for property assertions |
| 7 | Magic Numbers | `ReturnsCorrectAmount` | Medium | Needs knowledge of unit prices to add constants |
| 8 | Eager Test | `FullWorkflow_Succeeds` | High | Requires splitting into multiple focused tests |
| 9 | General Fixture | `_logger` | Low | Delete two lines |

Items 1–6 and 9 are quick mechanical fixes. Item 7 requires knowing the price catalog. Item 8 is the largest refactor but can wait until the high-severity issues are resolved.
